# Billy web — DEV-SERVER config (apps/web). Copy to `.env.development` (or `.env`).
#
# IMPORTANT: this file configures the LOCAL VITE DEV SERVER only (`pnpm dev`).
# It is NOT how the deployed app is configured — production reads its API/APP
# URLs at RUNTIME from window.__APP_CONFIG__ (deploy/config.js, bind-mounted),
# never from a build-time env. See apps/web/src/config.ts + the root README.
#
# In dev, the Vite server proxies /api, /public and /socket.io to the backend so
# the SPA stays same-origin (session cookies + WebSocket work, no CORS). Point
# this at wherever the backend is reachable from your host.

# Backend the dev server proxies to. The local Docker stack exposes the API via
# Traefik on :3480 (docker-compose.dev.yml). Change if you run the API elsewhere.
VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:3480
